Task
Split the array into two arrays: an array of even numbers and an array of odd numbers
An array containing numbers is given. Get two arrays: an array of even numbers and an array of odd numbers.
Write a separateEvenAndOdd function that takes a numeric array arr as an argument, returns an array containing an array of even numbers and an array of odd numbers in the form: [[array of even numbers], [array of odd numbers]].
Example:
• the separateEvenAndOdd ([- 2, -3, 7, 4) function must return [[-2, 4], [- 3, 7]];
• the separateEvenAndOdd ([4, 2]) function must return [[4, 2], []];
• the separateEvenAndOdd ([]) function must return [[], []].
Solution
function separateEvenAndOdd (arr) {
 let even = [];
  let odd = [];
  for (let el of arr) {
    if (el% 2 == 0) {
    even.push (el);
    }
    if (el% 2! == 0) {
    odd.push (el);
    }
  }
    return [even, odd];
} 
